+    "trader_investment_decision": "**Action**: Hold\n\n**Reasoning**: The analysts' research plan presents a balanced but cautious case for NVDA. The bear wins on valuation (forward multiples depend on 65%+ revenue growth from a $216B base, which is decelerating from 126% to 66%) and balance sheet quality ($5.5B write-down, goodwill surge to $20.8B, inventory doubling to $21.4B), creating asymmetric downside risk. The bull's strongest points\u2014$96.7B FCF, 44.8% FCF margin, and CUDA developer moat\u2014prevent a downgrade but don't justify adding exposure at current elevated levels. Technically, the stock sits at a critical decision point between $197 support and $216 resistance with conflicting signals (golden cross vs. negative MACD histogram and volume-decelerating bounce). The growth deceleration, margin cyclicality risk, and balance sheet warning signs warrant a defensive posture\u2014hold existing sizing and wait for a catalyst to break the range before committing new capital.\n\n**Stop Loss**: 197.0\n\n**Position Sizing**: Maintain current allocation; do not add exposure. Trim 25% if NVDA closes below $197 for two consecutive sessions. Add 10-15% only on a confirmed close above $217 on above-average volume.\n\nFINAL TRANSACTION PROPOSAL: **HOLD**",
